Fair-Trade Independent Tobacco Association's application to appeal the dismissal of its challenge to the cigarette sales ban has been dismissed by the Pretoria High Court. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The fight to lift the tobacco ban has suffered another blow in court. Fair-Trade Independent Tobacco Association's application to appeal the dismissal of its challenge to the cigarette sales ban has been dismissed by the Pretoria High Court. READ: Fita asks for leave to appeal tobacco ban National Coronavirus Command Council has been arguing that smokers posed a risk to the embattled healthcare system as the country fights COVID-19. The association is not giving up yet and is looking to file a petition for a right of appeal at the Supreme Court of Appeal.